<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97836430824089></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97836430824089><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4365&mid=97836430824089>mana to wis/int conversion</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4365&mid=97836430824089#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 1st 3:53 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>take the amount of mana an item gives you and multiply that by 5.  Then, take the number you get from that and divide it by your level.  That is the amount of int/wis that you would normally need to get that amount of mana.<br><br>so, the equation is:  mana = level * (int or wis) / 5.   or    int or wis = mana * 5 / level.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
